# Managed by the dotfiles bare repo (git-dir ~/.dotfiles, work-tree $HOME).
# Because the work-tree is $HOME, this guards against accidentally committing
# sensitive or runtime files. Tracked files are still added explicitly; this
# just makes a stray `config add -A` / `config add ~/.claude` safe.

# Claude Code: ignore everything under ~/.claude except the tracked config.
# (~/.claude holds credentials, conversation transcripts, memory, caches, logs.)
.claude/*
!.claude/CLAUDE.md
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/keybindings.json
!.claude/statusline-command.sh
